Reasoning: 
1. cs.IT (Information Theory) - The paper deals with the characterization of spectral efficiency in MIMO systems, which is a core topic in information theory. 
2. cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) - The paper focuses on downlink cellular systems, which are a key component of networking and internet architecture. 
3. cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) - The paper uses stochastic geometry to model the network, which is a common technique in social and information networks. 
4. cs.MA (Multiagent Systems) - The paper considers a single user being served by multiple antennas, which can be viewed as a multiagent system. 
5. cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory) - The paper discusses the optimal number of streams, which can be viewed as a game-theoretic problem.
